1 Overview
**********

‘sync-journals-bib’ walks a master BibTeX file, gathers the unique
journal names that appear in ‘journal’ or ‘journaltitle’ fields, and
compares them against the second slot of every triple in
‘org-ref-bibtex-journal-abbreviations’.  For each journal that is
missing from that table the package emits a ready-to-paste ‘add-to-list’
form.  When network access is available the package also fetches a CASSI
search result page and fills the third slot with the official Chemical
Abstracts Service abbreviation.


