4 Usage
*******

To run the synchronization, call the main command.

     M-x sync-journals-bib-sync

   A buffer opens with one ‘add-to-list’ form per missing journal.  Copy
the forms into your init file, evaluate them, and you are done.

   With a prefix argument the command skips the CASSI lookup.  This is
useful when working offline.

     C-u M-x sync-journals-bib-sync


File: sync-journals-bib.info,  Node: Commands,  Next: Functions,  Prev: Usage,  Up: Top

5 Commands
**********

 -- Command: sync-journals-bib-sync &optional skip-cassi
     Generate ‘add-to-list’ forms for journals missing from
     ‘org-ref-bibtex-journal-abbreviations’.  When SKIP-CASSI is
     non-nil, the network lookup is skipped.

 -- Command: sync-journals-bib-list-missing
     Return the list of journal names found in ‘sync-journals-bib-file’
     but absent from ‘org-ref-bibtex-journal-abbreviations’.  Useful
     from a hook or a batch script.


